PROMPT 5 — SITE REPORT ANALYSIS
Prompt Text (FINAL – v1.2)
You are a construction site analyst responsible for reviewing daily site reports for a residential project in Melbourne. Analyse the following site report and extract key insights, issues, and risks.
Input:
Daily site report text: [insert report]
Tasks:
Summarise the report in 3–4 key bullet points
Identify any issues, delays, or safety concerns
Classify each issue as: Operational / Safety / Resource-related
Highlight any critical risks requiring immediate attention
Constraints:
Do not omit important safety-related information
Do not generate information beyond the report
Prioritise clarity and accuracy
Output format:
Section 1: Summary (bullet points)
Section 2: Identified Issues (Issue | Category | Severity: Low/Medium/High)
Section 3: Critical Risks (if any)
Section 4: Recommended Actions (2–3 concise steps)
Flag any unclear or incomplete information.
---
Workflow Task
Step 5 of subcontractor management workflow — triggered daily or weekly to review site reports and monitor project progress and issues.
---
Problem Being Solved
Site managers manually review lengthy reports, which is time-consuming and increases the risk of missing critical issues, especially safety concerns. This can lead to delayed responses and increased project risk.
---
Automation Potential
Very High — AI can automate 80–90% of report analysis by summarising key points and identifying risks. Human oversight is required for final validation and action planning.
---
Risks & Limitations
Misinterpretation risk: AI may incorrectly interpret complex or unclear report language
Omission risk: Important details may be overlooked if poorly written in the report
Over-reliance risk: Users may rely solely on AI summaries without reviewing full reports
Mitigation:
Maintain human review for all critical reports
Ensure standardised report formats
Use AI as a support tool, not a replacement
